## 1. Executive Summary

Meridian Intelligence GmbH proposes a comprehensive, evidence-led monitoring solution for the European Parliament’s Office for Promotion of Parliamentary Democracy (OPPD) to map and track civil society organisations (CSOs) active in EU policy processes. In direct response to the transparency gaps identified in self-reported registers, our proposal aligns with the European Union’s "Defence of Democracy" framework by providing a high-fidelity intelligence layer. We offer the Parliament a robust mechanism to identify both registered and unregistered advocacy groups, ensuring a complete and inclusive overview of the actors shaping the European legislative landscape.

Our methodology centers on the proprietary Meridian Web Intelligence Pipeline, designed specifically to solve the "NGO Population Problem." Rather than relying on static NACE codes or voluntary disclosures, we deploy large-scale web-crawling and multilingual NLP classifiers to detect "policy signals" across the EU27 markets. By analyzing observable evidence—such as position papers, institutional interactions, and EU funding records—our system identifies "hidden actors" with a verified false-positive rate of <3%. 

The project will deliver a longitudinal knowledge base over a period of 30 months, beginning with a comprehensive Baseline Dataset of verified entities within the first eight months. This is followed by a continuous monitoring cycle providing quarterly technical progress reports and structured dataset updates.

